---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Shandapha | Modernize any app into a premium product surface"
  description="Shandapha is the UI modernization and continuity platform for safe premium upgrades, token mapping, merge-safe patches, and Doctor verification."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <article class="hero-card">
      <span class="eyebrow">UI modernization and continuity platform</span>
      <h1>Modernize any app into a premium product surface.</h1>
      <p>
        Shandapha upgrades messy products without asking teams to rewrite their stack. Import the
        brand, map semantic tokens, install premium pages, generate merge-safe patches, and verify
        the result with Doctor.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="cta primary" href="http://localhost:3002">Open Wizard</a>
        <a class="cta secondary" href="http://localhost:3004/playground">Preview Sandbox</a>
      </div>
      <div class="metric-grid">
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>Patch</strong>
          <p>Minimal diffs with reversible manifests and uninstall guidance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>Map</strong>
          <p>Import brand systems, infer semantic tokens, and keep CSS variables as runtime truth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="metric">
          <strong>Verify</strong>
          <p>Doctor catches missing providers, missing styles, WC wiring, and focus or contrast drift.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
    <aside class="stack-card">
      <h2>What teams keep</h2>
      <p>Your framework, your product logic, and your ownership model stay intact.</p>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>Inspect</strong>
        <p>Detect framework and styling shape across real existing apps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>Choose surfaces</strong>
        <p>Install real shells, templates, states, and premium product flows instead of loose widgets.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>Scale continuity</strong>
        <p>Contracts, registry metadata, governance, and cross-stack WC baselines keep the system durable.</p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Inspect. Map. Patch. Verify. Govern.</h2>
    <div class="step-grid">
      <div class="step">
        <strong>1. Inspect</strong>
        <p>Read the current app, surface framework seams, and detect styling truth.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>2. Map</strong>
        <p>Turn brand inputs and imported variables into semantic contracts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>3. Patch</strong>
        <p>Install premium shells, templates, and primitives with merge-safe output.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>4. Verify</strong>
        <p>Run Doctor for providers, theme vars, focus visibility, and patch manifest integrity.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>5. Govern</strong>
        <p>Roll out approved packs, templates, and policies without turning trust into magic.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <strong>6. Stay portable</strong>
        <p>React stays first-class DX while Web Components remain the cross-stack baseline.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
